                      @@@ CONSTRUCTOR @@@

@ Java constructor is special methods that is used to initialize objects
@ Constructor name must match with the class name
@ it can not have return type
@ Constructor is called when the object is created
@ We can overload it
@ We can create default constructor method.
@ it can have parameters which is used to initialize attributes. (You can have as many parameters as you want)
@ We can call a constructor inside of the other constructors.
@ We can call constructors in Super classes.

